Devon name is from Sherwood (Green) in Yarnscombe (Devon). These are well evidenced as medieval placenames, and there may be similar but unrecorded places that could account for the medieval surname in other counties such as East Yorkshire, Norfolk, Oxfordshire, and Sussex. <i>Sherwood</i> occurs in minor placenames in Berkshire, Hampshire, Hertfordshire, Kent, North Yorkshire, Sussex, and Wiltshire, but they are recorded only in modern times and in many cases will have been named from the surname or perhaps in imitation of 2 below. This name was established in Ireland in the 17th century. See also   Sherrard  .","English: habitational name from Sherwood Forest in Nottinghamshire (‘the shire wood’).","Americanized form of some Jewish name."],"variants":[{"name":"Sherrard","meanings":["English:","from an unrecorded Middle English personal name <i>Shirard</i> (Old English <i>Scīrheard</i>, composed of the elements <i>scīr</i> ‘bright’ and <i>heard</i> ‘hard, bold’). Alternatively, the name may be a nickname deriving from Middle English <i>shir</i> (Old English <i>scīr</i>) ‘bright, fair’, with the addition of the Anglo-Norman French suffix <i>-ard</i>.","local pronunciation of   Sherwood  , especially perhaps in Leicestershire, Kent, Lincolnshire, Norfolk, Sussex, and Yorkshire. It may also have been much confused with   Skerritt  . This name, or the name in 1 above, has been established in Ireland (Derry) since the 17th century, along with <i>Sherwood</i> (in most provinces)."]}]},{"name":"Rowlan","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Roland  , or a transferred use of the surname derived from that given name in the Middle Ages."],"variants":[{"name":"Roland","meanings":["From an Old French personal name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, from <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>land</i> ‘land, territory’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. In Old French literature it is borne by a legendary Frankish hero, a vassal of Charlemagne, whose exploits are told in the <i>Chanson de Roland</i>. The subject of the poem is Roland's death at the Battle of Roncesvalles in the Pyrenees in  778 , while protecting the rearguard of the Frankish army on its retreat from Spain. Roland is depicted in literature and legend as headstrong and impulsive. His devoted friendship with the prudent  Oliver  is also legendary."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Rowlan Shirwood was born in 1180, in Chorlton, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom. He married Mrs. Rowlan Shirwood in 1208, in Lancashire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"1180–":"1180–Surnud","1188–Female":"1188–Surnud","1210–Female":"1210–Surnud","1180–Male":"1180–Surnud","Abt 1210":"umbes 1210","1210":"1210","1188":"1188","1208":"1208","1180":"1180","Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Barlow, Chorlton, Lancashire, England":"Chorlton, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Chorlton, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Chorlton, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1180–":"1180–Kuollut","1188–Female":"1188–Kuollut","1210–Female":"1210–Kuollut","1180–Male":"1180–Kuollut","Abt 1210":"noin 1210","1210":"1210","1188":"1188","1208":"1208","1180":"1180","Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Barlow, Chorlton, Lancashire, England":"Chorlton, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Chorlton, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Chorlton, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1180–":"1180–Décédé","1188–Female":"1188–Décédée","1210–Female":"1210–Décédée","1180–Male":"1180–Décédé","Abt 1210":"environ 1210","1210":"1210","1188":"1188","1208":"1208","1180":"1180","Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Lancashire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Barlow, Chorlton, Lancashire, England":"Chorlton, Lancashire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Cho